  ANIMALS OF THE WORLD
============================================================

Name:         Snow Leopard
Scientific:   Panthera uncia
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Mountain
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     15 years
Weight:       55 kg
Status:       Vulnerable
Fact:         Cannot roar; uses long tail as blanket; leaps 15 meters

Name:         Mimic Octopus
Scientific:   Thaumoctopus mimicus
Class:        Cephalopoda
Habitat:      Shallow sea
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     1 years
Weight:       0.5 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Can mimic 15+ different species including lionfish and flatfish

Name:         Arctic Fox
Scientific:   Vulpes lagopus
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Arctic tundra
Diet:         Omnivore
Lifespan:     3 years
Weight:       3.5 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Fur changes color seasonally; survives -70 degrees Celsius

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Fermat's Last Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      aⁿ + bⁿ ≠ cⁿ for n>2
Applications: Advanced number theory, elliptic curves
Discoverer:   Fermat (conjecture); Wiles (proof) (1637)

Theorem/Law:  Central Limit Theorem
Branch:       Statistics
Formula:      Sample means approach normal distribution
Applications: Polling, quality control, finance
Discoverer:   Lyapunov (1901)

Theorem/Law:  Taylor Series
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      f(x) = sum of f^n(a)/n! * (x-a)^n
Applications: Numerical computation, signal processing
Discoverer:   Brook Taylor (1715)

